		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Two of the most powerful (but still easy to use) chip trackers I've ever seen are Raster Music Tracker and Goat Tracker
<br /><a href="http://raster.infos.cz/atari/rmt/rmt.htm" class="postlink">http://raster.infos.cz/atari/rmt/rmt.htm</a>
<br /><a href="http://covertbitops.c64.org/" class="postlink">http://covertbitops.c64.org/</a>
<br />
<br />I think they set great examples of how to utilize frame-based effects in a tracked format.
<br />
<br />That's what's really needed for good flexibility in a music engine.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
